feed.entry.author.name.label: maxrgwhite
feed.entry.updated.label: 2023-03-30T14:55:37-07:00
feed.entry.title.label: Brilliant app!
feed.entry.content.label: This app freely offers what multiple paid apps don’t. It offers you quick access to your basic guide or self-administered (through a beginning and ending bell) meditation of selected length, as well as playlists and other resources for specific meditations (e.g. sleep or stress reduction). I love this app and have recommended it to many people. Thank you for helping me so profoundly!

feed.entry.author.name.label: Nanchang Man
feed.entry.updated.label: 2023-03-22T16:18:12-07:00
feed.entry.title.label: Truly amazing.
feed.entry.content.label: This meditation app is nothing short of a positive and powerful life changer. It offers ways to help heal yourself in a world of stress and turmoil. It helps you to understand why you may feel anxiety/depression in your daily living and through meditation offers ways to address these and bring back hope and meaning to life. This isn’t just a small set of meditations to try but a whole range of ongoing teachings and challenges. The fact that the app is totally free is testament to the dedication, belief and hard work of a few volunteers in trying to bring a natural way of helping all of us to help ourselves develop happiness, compassion and purpose in everything we experience every day.

feed.entry.author.name.label: Tula Tina
feed.entry.updated.label: 2023-03-15T01:37:12-07:00
feed.entry.title.label: Love it and loath it.
feed.entry.content.label:
So much to like. Love the different choices and how you can build up your practice to suit you. Being able to choose a different person/ voice to listen too is great.
It’s not only simple to use but simple to understand so will suit everyone, so here comes the but …. It has become increasingly difficult to get onto. Loading is a big problem. I have tried many times over four days but only managed to get on twice. A meditation app really shouldn’t leave you frustrated.

feed.entry.updated.label: 2023-01-21T04:43:03-07:00
feed.entry.title.label: Changed my life!
feed.entry.content.label: I heard about meditation about a year ago, but always struggled to keep a consistent habit and didn’t really understand meditation and mindfulness. I thought if I had thoughts while meditating , I must be meditating wrong or I was just bad at meditation. Since I  downloaded  Medito 2 weeks ago, I have meditated every day. I also found it useful for the wide range of sessions from sleep to mindfulness to grief meditation and the daily meditation provides you with something new every day. I found it extremely useful to be able to do a short session of 3 minutes to help build up my meditation practice and the beginner courses have been very informative and relaxing as well as helping to grasp the basics of meditation. However, occasionally the servers go down so I would recommend downloading some sessions and turn your  phone onto airplane mode to see your downloaded sessions of the servers are down .

feed.entry.updated.label: 2023-01-17T13:22:53-07:00
feed.entry.title.label: Love it ..but
feed.entry.content.label:
I’m going to give this beautiful app five stars, because it truly deserves it. It is free and has really helped my sleep. And the app is free so you can obviously not expect perfection. Every now and then the app has just stopped working for me, but it was fine the next day. Sometimes the ‘background sounds’ don’t stop and just okay throughout the night after my meditation has finished. Over all though this app really has changed my life and I am so grateful for you Medito
Xx

feed.entry.content.label:
I’m going to give this beautiful app five stars, because it truly deserves it. It is free and has really helped my sleep. And the app is free so you can obviously not expect perfection. Every now and then the app has just stopped working for me, but it was fine the next day. Sometimes the ‘background sounds’ don’t stop and just okay throughout the night after my meditation has finished. Over all though this app really has changed my life and I am so grateful for you Medito
Xx

feed.entry.title.label: Helped me start my meditation journey
feed.entry.content.label: I’ve know about meditation for years and have always wanted to get involved. However the fact that every other app out there is paid I didn’t want to commit as I might not have liked it. With medito I started my journey over 2 months ago I’ve decreased my anxiety and depression feelings by a mile. And now I am preaching to everyone about meditation. As a young guy struggling with many addictions medito has helped me cut a lot of them out and I’m going to cut the last one out now too it’s a slow process but worth it. Highly recommend medito!

feed.entry.title.label: Helped me start my meditation journey
feed.entry.content.label: I’ve know about meditation for years and have always wanted to get involved. However the fact that every other app out there is paid I didn’t want to commit as I might not have liked it. With medito I started my journey over 2 months ago I’ve decreased my anxiety and depression feelings by a mile. And now I am preaching to everyone about meditation. As a young guy struggling with many addictions medito has helped me cut a lot of them out and I’m going to cut the last one out now too it’s a slow process but worth it. Highly recommend medito!

feed.entry.title.label: Perfect
feed.entry.content.label:
This app is perfect! It’s completely free as it’s a non-profit. There are loading issues frequently, however, this is due to the amount of people trying to get onto the app and they only have volunteers to fix the problem rather than employees . Although, they will notify you when issues occur, so you don’t think your phone is broken 😂. Overall, it’s a perfect app. It has many courses which are perfect for people starting meditation like I used to be as it teaches you everything you need to know and you’ll pick up the skill very quickly. 

It’s a great app made by great people. Would highly recommend!

feed.entry.title.label: I love this app
feed.entry.content.label:
I love this app. It’s useful and free!

They’ve had some loading issues in jan 2023 and I guess that’s what happens when tens of thousands of people take up meditating as a new year’s resolution and turn to a comprehensive free app. So I couldn’t load this one day and went to YouTube for a guided meditation instead

Let me tell you JUST show annoying that was. Saccharine, sickly sweet, annoying voice, random interjections when the voice SAID they were going to leave me to meditate. 

I am so so relieved that the app is back today and I can go back to my regular calm sensible person and I can progress through again. I really appreciate how hard these folks are working to provide something free and fix the problems at speed. 

Consider donating to them if you want things fixed faster :)

feed.entry.title.label: Glitch
feed.entry.content.label:
Usually the most amazing app, use it very frequently and find it to be helpful with anxiety and calming down . However, the app seems to have glitched, I open it an it shows a grey screen saying good eveing and a dark grey saying packs - nothing is showing up on the actual screen in terms of mediation and for an app that’s supposed to be calming I find this issue very frustrating. 
Tried uninstalling and reinstalling and stil nothing.

feed.entry.title.label: I really do reccomend
feed.entry.content.label:
I have never before written a review on the apple store for an app but i truly believe more people should know about this app. 

This app brings a free, high quality service to the app store, with its different guides and even narrators of which you can choose.

I have been using this app for a while now and it has really helped me to calm me down and set off on a good start.

I really do reccomend

feed.entry.title.label: Nothing loads, blank screens n spooling
feed.entry.content.label: Really disappointed. All geared up to meditate last two mornings and none of the sessions will open. I’ve tried opening ‘learning to sit’ and ‘mindfulness’ sessions. Today it took 5 minutes to open. It is not my internet. Time is precious, especially first thing in morning. Also, it’s not great for the mind to be having troubles with an app for mindfulness. Otherwise this would be 5 stars
